<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8255] MiniSolrCloudCluster doesn&apos;t use a thread-safe list for its jetties</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8255</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MiniSolrCloudCluster uses a LinkedList&amp;lt;&amp;gt; to hold its jetties.  However, multi-threaded startup can break this because the list isn&apos;t thread safe.  We should use CopyOnWriteArrayList instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See for example &lt;a href=&quot;http://jenkins.thetaphi.de/job/Lucene-Solr-trunk-Linux/14819/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jenkins.thetaphi.de/job/Lucene-Solr-trunk-Linux/14819/&lt;/a&gt;, which starts up 5 nodes but then only has 4 entries in its jetty list, causing assertion errors and thread leaks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12911502">SOLR-8255</key>
